definition.value: A glucotetraose consisting of three alpha-D-glucopyranosyl residues and a beta-D-glucopyranosyl residue joined in sequence by (1->4) glycosidic bonds.
An alpha-D-Galp-(1->6)-D-Galp in which the carbon bearing the anomeric hydroxy group has alpha configuration.
A glycosyl alditol consisting of alpha-D-galactopyranose and D-glucitol residues joined in sequence by a (1->6) glycosidic bond.

A linear amino tetrasaccharide consisting of alpha-neuraminyl, beta-D-galactosyl and N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl residues with at the reducing end beta-D-galactose linked in a (2->3), (1->3) and (1->4) sequence.
